Amnesty International today issued a series of recommendations to newly elected Honduran President Porfirio Lobo to repair the damage done to human rights since the June 2009 coup d’état, which left hundreds injured by the army and National Police, and also forced about 870 officials – judges, prosecutors, defense lawyers and law students – into exile.
Amnesty also recommended the immediate replacement of the incumbent Attorney General with a human rights law expert.
Amnesty International (AI) felt it is crucial to establish the reason for the coup immediately – so that appropriate steps can be taken to investigate, indict and bring the people responsible before the law, and recommend the recomposition of a National Peace Commission along with the appropriate human rights follow-up mechanisms;
That the Attorney General launch immediate investigations into the mining sector – the main driver behind the coup – and the expansion of the army and military equipment (as well as the removal of the army chief responsible for the coup) – and bring those responsible for the coup before the law;
AI recommended reconstituting a (Honduran) National Peace

